<p><strong>The Flea Palace: A Comprehensive Guide</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is the Flea Palace?</strong></p>
<p>The Flea Palace is a historic building located in Hobart, Tasmania. It was built in the 1840s and originally housed a flea market. In the 1990s, it was renovated and converted into a hub for independent traders and artists. Today, it offers a diverse range of stalls featuring handmade crafts, vintage clothing, antiques, and unique gifts.</p>
<p><strong>2. What is the Flea Market like?</strong></p>
<p>The Flea Market at the Flea Palace is a lively and eclectic space where you can find a wide variety of items. Vendors offer everything from hand-painted ceramics to repurposed furniture, from vintage records to locally made jewelry. The market is open on Saturdays from 9 am to 4 pm and is a great place to browse and support local businesses.</p>
<p><strong>3. Are there other activities at the Flea Palace?</strong></p>
<p>In addition to the Flea Market, the Flea Palace also hosts regular events and exhibitions. You can find everything from live music to art workshops to pop-up shops. The building also has a caf√© where you can enjoy coffee, tea, and light snacks.</p>
<p><strong>4. How can I learn more about the Flea Palace?</strong></p>
<p>The best way to learn more about the Flea Palace is to visit the official website (<a href="https://fleapalacehobart.com/">https://fleapalacehobart.com/</a>). You can also follow them on social media (Facebook: @fleapalacehobart, Instagram: @flea_palace_hobart) for updates on upcoming events and new vendors.</p>
<p><strong>5. Where is the Flea Palace located?</strong></p>
<p>The Flea Palace is located at 34 Elizabeth Street, Hobart, Tasmania 7000. It is easily accessible by public transport or car. There is paid parking available nearby.</p>